<TITLE> RAB arrests 'inter-district crime gang' in Savar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, July 9 (bdnews24.com)RAB arrested 18 suspected members of an 'inter-district crime gang' in Savar on Thursday. RAB-4 Savar camp commander Lt Commander Ariful Islam told bdnews24.com that the gang was preparing for a robbery on the Hemayetpur-Shingair highway. He said RAB arrested the suspects, aged between 18 and 42, on a tip-off. They also seized a luxury coach being used by the gang as well as arms, cash and mobile-phone sets. The arrestees were named as 'Bachchu', 18, 'Based', 25, 'Aziz', 32, 'Siraj', 25, Korban Ali, 22, 'Rezaul', 27, Abdul Alim, 45, Rais Miah, 29, 'Mizan', 28, Momin Hossain, 22, 'Mostafa', 22, Mizanur Rahman, 35, Alim Molla, 28, 'Khalil', 42, 'Sumon', 34, Sakhawat Hossain, 25, 'Rahim', 30 and Kader, 42. A one-shooter gun, two ramdas (long, curve-bladed knives), a machete, a dagger, Tk 20,000 in cash and nine mobile-phone sets were recovered from their possession. A case was filed with Savar Police Station. bdn
